The paper discusses the SP theory of intelligence, which is a theory of computing and has potential to simplify and integrate structures and processes in computing systems. It also discusses various AI-related alternatives such as deep learning, Bayesian networks, and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.LG (machine learning), cs.NE (neural networks), cs.CC (computational complexity), and cs.SY (systems and control).
